e8e76d7b-df7c-4333-a55f-34e495e7e9fa	9vJRopau0g0	Unknown	Unknown	0	[{"text": "About a year ago, I asked my YouTube followers to play a simple computer programming puzzle", "start": 19.64, "duration": 5.259999999999998}, {"text": "that I made with a The object of the puzzle was to get your car across the maze", "start": 24.8, "duration": 4.82}, {"text": "by arranging these code blocks that represent typical computer programming operations such as", "start": 30, "duration": 5.380000000000003}, {"text": "if-else statements and while loops. Once you thought you had a good code, you would hit run", "start": 35.04, "duration": 5.219999999999999}, {"text": "and your car would move based on the commands you had in the program. So I asked my YouTube", "start": 40.36, "duration": 5.420000000000002}, {"text": "followers to play it because I said I wanted to prove that anyone from any background could learn", "start": 45.64, "duration": 5.380000000000003}, {"text": "to code. 50,000 of them took the challenge and attempted the puzzle.", "start": 50.72, "duration": 4.660000000000004}, {"text": "But the truth was that I didn't actually care about proving that anyone could learn to code.", "start": 56.48, "duration": 4.8600000000000065}, {"text": "What they didn't know is that we actually randomly served up two slightly different versions", "start": 61.68, "duration": 5.020000000000003}, {"text": "of the In one version, if you hit run and you weren't successful, you didn't lose", "start": 66.76, "duration": 5.259999999999991}, {"text": "any of your starting 200 points. We showed you this message. However, in the other", "start": 71.88, "duration": 5.38000000000001}, {"text": "version, if you hit run and again you weren't successful, we showed this slightly different message", "start": 77.04, "duration": 5.459999999999994}, {"text": "stating that you lost five points from your starting 200 points. That was the only difference.", "start": 82.96, "duration": 5.140000000000001}, {"text": "In one version, if you failed, we simply took away five, no value in the real world, no one", "start": 88.96, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "will ever see these completely meaningless fake internet", "start": 94.12, "duration": 2.9399999999999977}, {"text": "That minor difference is crucial to keep in mind for the results I'm about to show you", "start": 98.72, "duration": 5.299999999999997}, {"text": "from the 50,000 data points we For those who were penalized for failed attempts,", "start": 103.84, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "their success rate was around", "start": 109.72, "duration": 1.5400000000000063}, {"text": "For those who were not penalized, their success rate was 68%.", "start": 113.2, "duration": 3.6199999999999903}, {"text": "That statistically significant 16% was really surprising and almost seemed", "start": 119.08, "duration": 5.460000000000008}, {"text": "too hard to believe until we looked at another piece of data that we collected. Which was attempts to", "start": 124.28, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "solve before finding success. It's shown in orange right here. So those who didn't see failing in a negative", "start": 129.399, "duration": 5.461000000000013}, {"text": "light nearly had two and a half times more attempts to solve the puzzle. As a result,", "start": 134.76, "duration": 5.300000000000011}, {"text": "naturally they saw more success and therefore learned more. So if you think about that and sort of unpack", "start": 139.92, "duration": 5.340000000000003}, {"text": "these results, the trick to learning more and having more success is finding the right way", "start": 145.28, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "to frame the learning process. And this observation seemed really profound to me. It made me", "start": 150.44, "duration": 5.460000000000008}, {"text": "wonder, what if you just framed the learning process in such a way that you didn't concern yourself with failure?", "start": 155.48, "duration": 5.460000000000008}, {"text": "How much more successful could you be? How much more could you learn? And the next thought was that if this is a real", "start": 161.56, "duration": 5.460000000000008}, {"text": "effect, clearly there must be some evidence for this in real life. It made me think of toddlers.", "start": 166.72, "duration": 4.5800000000000125}, {"text": "It's my boy. I helped make that.", "start": 172.52, "duration": 1.6599999999999966}, {"text": "They are constantly trying new things and they certainly aren't concerned with failure.", "start": 176.52, "duration": 4.899999999999977}, {"text": "When my son learned to walk, he didn't think about how dumb he might look if he fell down. And as his parents,", "start": 181.6, "duration": 5.300000000000011}, {"text": "we didn't punish him if he wasn't successful either. The focus was always on the end goal and", "start": 186.8, "duration": 5.4599999999999795}, {"text": "we celebrated the successes with him. As a result of constantly failing", "start": 191.92, "duration": 5.380000000000024}, {"text": "and trying and discovering new things during that phases of our life, we discover so many", "start": 197.44, "duration": 5.420000000000016}, {"text": "more new capabilities within ourselves and it's not even close to any other time in our life.", "start": 202.6, "duration": 4.939999999999998}, {"text": "But maybe using a toddler is sort of cheating because their brains are different than ours.", "start": 209.2, "duration": 4.060000000000002}, {"text": "To make the case that perhaps they aren't that different than us, I'd like to tell you about a plumber", "start": 214.6, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "I first met when I was 8 years old. He was Italian.", "start": 220.24, "duration": 2.6200000000000045}, {"text": "When Super Mario Brothers came out, my friends and I became obsessed. Like we wanted to get", "start": 228.16, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "to the castle and rescue the beautiful Princess Peach from the evil Bowser. We'd get to school and ask each other", "start": 233.24, "duration": 5.340000000000003}, {"text": "like, \\"Dude, what level did you make it to? Did you pass the game?\\" We never asked each other about details", "start": 238.28, "duration": 4.939999999999998}, {"text": "on all the different ways we might have When it comes to games like this, no one ever picks up the controller", "start": 243.36, "duration": 5.339999999999975}, {"text": "for the first time and then after jumping into a pit thinks, \\"I'm so ashamed. That was such a failure.\\"", "start": 248.56, "duration": 4.780000000000001}, {"text": "And they never want to try again, right? What really happens is they think, \\"Oh, I've got to remember, there's a pit right there.", "start": 253.64, "duration": 5.420000000000016}, {"text": "So I think next time I'm going to come out with a little more speed. I'm going to jump a little bit later.\\" The focus and the obsession", "start": 259.16, "duration": 5.099999999999966}, {"text": "is about beating the game, not how dumb you might look if you get hit by a sliding green shell.", "start": 264.72, "duration": 4.979999999999961}, {"text": "And as a direct result of that attitude, of learning from but not being focused on the failures,", "start": 270.08, "duration": 5.259999999999991}, {"text": "we got really good and we learned a ton in a very short amount of time. We were the right side of this", "start": 275.88, "duration": 5.4599999999999795}, {"text": "This is what I call the Super Mario effect. Focusing on the princess and not the pits", "start": 282.36, "duration": 5.21999999999997}, {"text": "to stick with the task and to learn more. This caused me to reflect and realize that there", "start": 288.04, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "were lots of other examples from my own personal experience where this attitude of life gamification,", "start": 293.16, "duration": 4.4599999999999795}, {"text": "this Super Mario effect, led to more success and therefore more learning.", "start": 298.28, "duration": 4.300000000000011}, {"text": "So I have a science YouTube channel where I will sometimes use my engineering skills to build things such", "start": 303.84, "duration": 4.7000000000000455}, {"text": "the world's largest Super Soaker", "start": 310.16, "duration": 1.6199999999999477}, {"text": "or the Guinness World Record world's LARGEST NERF GUN", "start": 314.28, "duration": 2.2600000000000477}, {"text": "OR MAYBE THE SNOWBALL MACHINE GUN", "start": 323.8, "duration": 2.0600000000000023}, {"text": "FASHIONED FROM A LEAF BLOWER.", "start": 328.48, "duration": 1.5}, {"text": "That's my niece.", "start": 332.4, "duration": 1.0200000000000387}, {"text": "Those are my nephews. Uh I haven't quite figured it out, but when it comes to me their uncle,", "start": 335.88, "duration": 5.420000000000016}, {"text": "they seem to have some trust issues.", "start": 341.08, "duration": 1.6999999999999886}, {"text": "these builds usually take me about two to three months, but there was one that took me three years.", "start": 348.72, "duration": 5.419999999999959}, {"text": "Basically, I wanted to make a dartboard where you could get a bull's-eye every time. The idea was that if you throw", "start": 354.84, "duration": 5.340000000000032}, {"text": "a dart, we could like track it through the air and then we'd move the board sort of like catch a bull's-eye.", "start": 359.96, "duration": 4.460000000000036}, {"text": "And so once we did the math, we realized that if we wanted to track the dart for a typical like game of darts,", "start": 366.32, "duration": 5.139999999999986}, {"text": "typical we would basically have to both track the dart and to move", "start": 371.56, "duration": 5.339999999999975}, {"text": "the board the same amount of time it takes for a human to blink once. No big deal, right?", "start": 376.6, "duration": 4.859999999999957}, {"text": "So I'm not going to bore you with all the details and the failures and the setbacks from a lot of metaphorical sliding green", "start": 381.92, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "shells and those pesky Hammer Head Bros. But eventually we figured out", "start": 387.04, "duration": 4.899999999999977}, {"text": "it would take something that looks like this, which is six stepper motors and motion controllers, a Vicon motion", "start": 392.2, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "capture system with six cameras, and just a ton of tweaking and rewriting the code.", "start": 397.36, "duration": 4.779999999999973}, {"text": "But finally, eventually we arrived here.", "start": 402.76, "duration": 2.259999999999991}, {"text": "What's interesting is when I look back on that process, like I can honestly say my attitude towards that", "start": 418.16, "duration": 5.4599999999999795}, {"text": "was the same attitude I had toward like rescuing the princess from Bowser.", "start": 423.76, "duration": 4.860000000000014}, {"text": "Like of course each failure and setback sucked. It stung. But it was no different than like falling", "start": 428.8, "duration": 5.4599999999999795}, {"text": "in that pit on level 8-1 and they're like, \\"Ah!\\" And you got to go back to the level and try again. Like it was always like,", "start": 434.08, "duration": 5.420000000000016}, {"text": "\\"Okay, that sucked, but what did we learn from that? Like what can we do next for it? Let's hit it", "start": 439.2, "duration": 5.060000000000002}, {"text": "And this concept of life gamification is more than just like have a positive attitude, right? Or never", "start": 445.28, "duration": 5.300000000000011}, {"text": "give up. Because those sort of imply you're having to endure against your true desire to quit.", "start": 450.36, "duration": 5.060000000000002}, {"text": "I feel like when you frame a challenge or a learning process in the way I'm describing, you actually want to do it.", "start": 456, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "It feels natural to ignore the failures and try again. In the same way a toddler will", "start": 461.6, "duration": 5.339999999999975}, {"text": "want to get up and try and walk again. Or in the same way you want to keep playing Super Mario", "start": 466.72, "duration": 5.339999999999975}, {"text": "Brothers. Or in the same way the group on the right had a desire to stick with that puzzle", "start": 471.84, "duration": 5.260000000000048}, {"text": "two and a half times longer. They weren't getting paid to do that. Nobody was forcing them or watching", "start": 477.36, "duration": 5.339999999999975}, {"text": "them. It was just them on their computer alone in their house. Their outlook made it so", "start": 482.64, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "they wanted to keep trying and learning. And the icing on the cake for the dartboard was I took it on", "start": 487.72, "duration": 5.419999999999959}, {"text": "Jimmy Kimmel and challenged him to a game of darts. And I'll just set this clip up by saying two things. The first", "start": 492.8, "duration": 5.099999999999966}, {"text": "is we also had a mode on the board where if your buddy had it and threw a dart, the board would move the other way.", "start": 498.08, "duration": 5.100000000000023}, {"text": "And the second is that we couldn't get this thing working during rehearsal and", "start": 504.96, "duration": 5.060000000000002}, {"text": "it was just barely kind of creeping along. I get up to stand in the elevator, which is the door that moves up before you go down", "start": 510.76, "duration": 5.419999999999959}, {"text": "out on stage. I look to the right, all six cameras had failed. So my buddy John is feverishly like restarting", "start": 516.24, "duration": 5.418999999999983}, {"text": "all the cameras as I'm going out on the stage knowing this and there's like four things in bits", "start": 521.64, "duration": 4.980000000000018}, {"text": "and I work up to the dartboard as the sort of grand finale. So just keep that in mind as this clip", "start": 526.96, "duration": 5.459999999999923}, {"text": "starts. Like that's where my head space is. Three freaking years and it comes down to this moment.", "start": 532.16, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "What you're going to do is you're going to give this start to your buddy and you're going to challenge him just to like", "start": 538.16, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "hit the board. Yeah. Okay. All right.", "start": 543.76, "duration": 2.7799999999999727}, {"text": "All right, hotshot. You going to double or nothing? All right, yeah, yeah. All right. Ready?", "start": 550.56, "duration": 4.340000000000032}, {"text": "Okay. All right. And so then I step up it automatically. That's", "start": 557.24, "duration": 5.460000000000036}, {"text": "right. That's right. Yeah. I step up. Here we go.", "start": 562.32, "duration": 4.6200000000000045}, {"text": "Fake it till you make it. I will say in all of our testing, literally, we never", "start": 572.68, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "had a dead center bull's-eye as much as that one right there. And so like after that, I haven't even touched the", "start": 578, "duration": 5.460000000000036}, {"text": "board since. I'm like, \\"I'm so done with it.\\"", "start": 583.04, "duration": 2.1800000000000637}, {"text": "And I really believe that if you reframe like the challenges, it can make all the difference. I have", "start": 588.24, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "a simple thought experiment to sort of showcase this. Let's say I gave you a test and it had instructions", "start": 593.28, "duration": 4.980000000000018}, {"text": "on it that you would carry out. And to do that, it had sort of buttons like this. And the", "start": 598.44, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "instructions would say something like push button three for 5 seconds, and then push button six for 1 second, then", "start": 603.48, "duration": 5.460000000000036}, {"text": "push buttons three and five for six seconds, and so on. And unless you carried out the instructions on page one exactly,", "start": 608.6, "duration": 5.340000000000032}, {"text": "you couldn't see the other 32 pages of the test. How much would I have to pay you to take that", "start": 614.16, "duration": 5.340000000000032}, {"text": "test for an hour? Now, suppose I change the word test here to game,", "start": 619.2, "duration": 5.059999999999945}, {"text": "and I rotated this. And for the input device, I shrunk the buttons and moved them", "start": 624.68, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "here. And I gave it a cool paint job. And maybe different button", "start": 629.76, "duration": 4.019999999999982}, {"text": "And then instead of using words, I represented the tasks you needed to accomplish visually like this.", "start": 634.84, "duration": 5.2999999999999545}, {"text": "Note the output is the exact same. You have to push these buttons in a very specific manner to", "start": 641.24, "duration": 5.460000000000036}, {"text": "move on to the next page, or level as it were. Now, picture it's 1986.", "start": 646.36, "duration": 4.3799999999999955}, {"text": "How much would you pay me to take this test just for an If you have", "start": 651.6, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "a very bad imagination, here's a hint to the right answer. I know, I WAS THERE. NINTENDO!", "start": 656.72, "duration": 4.619000000000028}, {"text": "THANK YOU. THANK YOU.", "start": 665.08, "duration": 3.019999999999982}, {"text": "OH, DON'T GO RODNEY. DON'T PLAY WITH IT.", "start": 670.52, "duration": 2.5399999999999636}, {"text": "That has to be the greatest YouTube clip of all time.", "start": 675.2, "duration": 2.6200000000000045}, {"text": "So, as a science YouTuber, sometimes I feel people have framed the act of learning science", "start": 679.68, "duration": 4.940000000000055}, {"text": "in a negative way. It's been taught poorly, so it feels scary to them. It feels something", "start": 684.72, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "more like this. And my approach is to take the same physics lessons you might have hated,", "start": 689.96, "duration": 4.939999999999941}, {"text": "and to try and sort of trick you into learning something through something cool.", "start": 695.24, "duration": 5.220000000000027}, {"text": "Basically, to go from this to this.", "start": 700.68, "duration": 2.580000000000041}, {"text": "So, for example, in this video I made a hot tub with liquefied sand. And uh", "start": 704.96, "duration": 5.259999999999991}, {"text": "this is another one of my nephews with unexplained trust issues.", "start": 710.32, "duration": 3.2199999999999136}, {"text": "I explained in the video that it's a fluidized bed, and then we talk about the principle of buoyancy and how it makes", "start": 716.08, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "the whole thing work. And I use several examples, like, you know, the blow dryer with a ping pong ball like this.", "start": 721.28, "duration": 5.180000000000064}, {"text": "I like to think my approach to science is similar to velociraptor hunting patterns. So,", "start": 726.8, "duration": 5.180000000000064}, {"text": "I get people to come in with something cool and amazing like the sand hot tub. And then when they least", "start": 732.2, "duration": 5.17999999999995}, {"text": "expect it,", "start": 737.4, "duration": 1.0600000000000591}, {"text": "Clever girl.", "start": 741.6, "duration": 1.0199999999999818}, {"text": "And then the analogy breaks down a little bit right there at the end. But", "start": 744.44, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "by reframing the learning process, and focusing on the cool end goal, the fear of failure", "start": 749.48, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "is often taken off the table, and learning just comes more I'll close with", "start": 754.839, "duration": 5.460999999999899}, {"text": "this thought. Someone came up with this cartoon, and I totally love it. This is so", "start": 759.92, "duration": 5.460000000000036}, {"text": "true, but often in life we tell ourselves that the top version is what we want. That's what we expect.", "start": 765.04, "duration": 5.340000000000032}, {"text": "But then something happens. Maybe it's a really bad grade on a test, or a meeting with a client that goes horribly wrong.", "start": 771.24, "duration": 5.340000000000032}, {"text": "Maybe it's a bad breakup. Maybe we miss a wide open shot. Some kind of green shell hits you.", "start": 776.72, "duration": 5.2999999999999545}, {"text": "And so at that first setback or sign of failure, doubt creeps in. We tell ourselves we're not good enough. We're not", "start": 782.6, "duration": 5.419999999999959}, {"text": "smart enough. And yet, if the bottom rectangle here is a game where now your bike's", "start": 787.72, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "crashed, and you have to get your bike across to the flag, it's not oh, I hit these rocks. I'm", "start": 793, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "just going to leave my bike here. I'm not good enough, and you quit and walk away. You see that flag to the right, and you're like, nah.", "start": 798.08, "duration": 5.419999999999959}, {"text": "Like, what did I just learn? Like, okay. Next time, I got to come out with more speed, and I'm going to I'm going to lift the front", "start": 803.48, "duration": 5.419999999999959}, {"text": "of my bike up. You want to try it again. You're immediately excited to go for it We sort", "start": 808.6, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "of tell ourselves we want our life's challenges to look like the top one, but that's boring. If that", "start": 813.68, "duration": 5.460000000000036}, {"text": "were a real video game, or book, or or movie that went out to the market, it would be a total failure.", "start": 818.8, "duration": 4.900000000000091}, {"text": "Nobody would buy it. Where's the risk and the reward? Where's the challenge? There's no feeling of satisfaction.", "start": 824.36, "duration": 5.100000000000023}, {"text": "The bottom picture is real life, and that's not a bug. That's a feature.", "start": 830.12, "duration": 4.3799999999999955}, {"text": "Think about anything that means anything to you in life, whether it's a degree, a relationship with a friend, or", "start": 835.76, "duration": 5.460000000000036}, {"text": "someone in your family, maybe a professional accomplishment. I can guarantee you it came", "start": 841.16, "duration": 5.300000000000068}, {"text": "from something that looks like the bottom, and not the top. Failing and failing and failing", "start": 846.24, "duration": 5.220000000000027}, {"text": "and eventually succeeding to the point that it now holds value. Just like the", "start": 851.4, "duration": 5.5}, {"text": "most meaningful high fives of my adolescence were those when I said, \\"Dude, I finally beat", "start": 856.48, "duration": 5.3799999999999955}, {"text": "Bowser last night.\\"", "start": 861.959, "duration": 1.2210000000000036}, {"text": "I feel like a lot of the successes in my life have come down to the Super Mario effect. And while framing challenges", "start": 865.2, "duration": 5.2999999999999545}, {"text": "like this has worked for me, of course results may vary. Everyone is going to be different,", "start": 870.52, "duration": 4.779999999999973}, {"text": "and I don't know exactly what it looks like for you to take this principle and map it into your life.", "start": 875.56, "duration": 4.940000000000055}, {"text": "But if we got these very real results from a very different cross section of very", "start": 880.72, "duration": 5.259999999999991}, {"text": "unique people, clearly I'm not alone. There's some universal principle at play here.", "start": 885.76, "duration": 5.139999999999986}, {"text": "By shifting your focus to the princess, and treating your life's challenges like video games, you can trick", "start": 891.12, "duration": 5.2999999999999545}, {"text": "your brain, and actually learn more and see more success. Thank you.", "start": 896.28, "duration": 3.9600000000000364}]	2026